---
const sections = [
  {
    id: "discovery",
    title: "Discovery",
    body: `In 2021, paleontologists working with Theropoda Expeditions uncovered a remarkably complete <em>Tyrannosaurus rex</em> on private ranchland in western South Dakota. The land belonged to cattle rancher Gary "Gus" Licking, who had noticed teeth and bone fragments for years. The team named the specimen <strong>Gus</strong> in his honor after he died during the excavation.`,
  },
  {
    id: "specimen",
    title: "The specimen",
    body: `Gus comprises 183 fossil bones—roughly 82% of the skeleton by bone count. The mount stands about 12.5 feet tall and 38 feet long, with a skull over four feet in length. Field excavation took roughly three summers; laboratory preparation took about three more.`,
  },
  {
    id: "auction",
    title: "The auction",
    body: `Sotheby's will offer Gus in its Natural History auction in New York on <strong>14 July 2026</strong>, with a presale estimate of <strong>$20–30 million</strong>—among the highest ever placed on a dinosaur skeleton. Public viewing at Sotheby's galleries begins 1 July 2026.`,
  },
  {
    id: "public-trust",
    title: "Why public trust matters",
    body: `When scientifically significant fossils enter private collections, researchers may lose reliable access to the specimen. Sue—the first auctioned <em>T. rex</em>—reached Chicago's Field Museum through a consortium of institutions and donors, not a single private buyer. This campaign advocates for the same outcome for Gus: permanent stewardship where the public and scientists can study and learn.`,
  },
];
---

<section class="dossier" id="dossier" aria-labelledby="dossier-heading">
  <div class="container dossier__layout">
    <div class="dossier__intro">
      <h2 id="dossier-heading" class="display dossier__title">Dossier</h2>
      <p class="dossier__lede">
        Public facts drawn from press coverage and auction listings. Not affiliated with Sotheby's or Theropoda Expeditions.
      </p>
      <figure class="dossier__figure">
        <img
          src="/images/gus-skeleton-scale.jpeg"
          alt="Person standing beside the mounted Gus skeleton for scale"
          loading="lazy"
          width="1200"
          height="800"
        />
        <figcaption>Scale of the mount — western South Dakota excavation.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="dossier__accordion">
      {
        sections.map((section, i) => (
          <details class="dossier__panel" id={`dossier-${section.id}`} open={i === 0}>
            <summary>{section.title}</summary>
            <div class="dossier__body" set:html={section.body} />
          </details>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .dossier {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--parchment) 70%, var(--bone));
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--clay) 30%, transparent);
  }

  .dossier__layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.1fr;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .dossier__title {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  .dossier__lede {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    color: var(--clay);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }

  .dossier__figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dossier__figure img {
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--clay) 35%, transparent);
  }

  .dossier__figure figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--clay);
  }

  .dossier__panel {
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--clay) 35%, transparent);
  }

  .dossier__panel summary {
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .dossier__panel summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .dossier__body {
    padding: 0 0 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
  }

  .dossier__body :global(p) {
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .dossier__layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
